comments: Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in Hunter's (ATL) path and does not deliver contact.
DeRozan (CHI) is retreating alongside Murray's (ATL) path and absorbs the marginal body contact as they come together during the drive.
Vucevic (CHI) and Okongwu (ATL) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in Murray's (ATL) path and does not deliver contact.
Hunter (ATL) establishes himself in Dosunmu's (CHI) path and absorbs the contact to his upper body prior to marginal leg contact occurring as Dosunmu goes over the pick.
Okongwu (ATL) engages and disengages with Vucevic (CHI) as Vucevic moves to set the pick.
Murray (ATL) immediately slides his hand off of Vucevic's (CHI) side and marginal contact occurs during the pick.
Hunter (ATL) extends slightly as he establishes his screening position and he avoids making contact with Dosunmu (CHI) as the pick is set.
Dosunmu's (CHI) left arm comes forward slightly prior to marginal contact occurring with Young's (ATL) right side/arm at the end of the drive.
Dosunmu (CHI) legally contests Okongwu's (ATL) dunk attempt.
Okongwu (ATL) engages and disengages with Vucevic (CHI) as Vucevic moves to set the pick.
Vucevic (CHI) is firming up over his left foot and does not deliver contact as he sets the pick on Hunter (ATL).
Okongwu (ATL) avoids making contact with DeRozan (CHI) and legally contests the jump shot attempt.
Dosunmu (CHI) brings his left forearm toward Young's (ATL) right side and marginal contact occurs as Young drives inside the perimeter.
Williams (CHI) and Vucevic (CHI) avoid making contact with Okongwu (ATL) during the alley-oop attempt.
Okongwu (ATL) makes contact with the ball while it is still in the imaginary cylinder above the rim.
Hunter (ATL) engages and disengages with DeRozan (CHI) during the inbound.
Hunter (ATL) legally contests DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Williams (CHI) maintains a rested forearm on Collins' (ATL) back and marginal contact occurs as Collins elevates to retrieve the ball, which he loses control of.
Collins (ATL) brushes Dosunmu's (CHI) front and marginal contact occurs during Dosunmu's upward shooting motion. Bogdanovic (ATL) jumps alongside Dosunmu and legally contests the layup attempt.
